-- Thailand Stocks: Indorama Ventures, Lee Feed Mill, S. Khonkaen
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-03-06T05:41:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/indorama-krungthai-card-lee-feed-mill-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand   trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. break in
Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.2 percent to 1,159.67.  Indorama Ventures Pcl (IVL)  , a Thai polyester maker,
gained 1.9 percent to 40 baht, a second day of gains. The
company acquired a factory belonging to PT Polypet Karyapersada
in  Indonesia , it said in a filing to the stock exchange. The
facility has a production capacity of 100,800 metric tons per
year, it said. Indorama will also benefit from a 6 percent
increase in cotton prices overnight, Maybank Kim Eng Securities
(Thailand) Pcl wrote in a report today.  Lee Feed Mill Pcl (LEE)  , an animal-feed producer,
climbed 1 percent to 4.22 baht, set for the highest close since
January 2004. The company will pay a dividend of 0.21 baht a
share, it said in a regulatory filing.  S. Khonkaen Foods Pcl (SORKON)  , a producer of processed
meat and sausages, slid 56 percent to 39.75 baht, a record drop.
Investors who buy shares today won’t be entitled to the
company’s one-for-two rights offer, the company said in a
regulatory filing on Feb. 27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
